# REQUIRED FOR EVERY INTERACTION:

1. Read .cursor/icr.mdx at the start of each interaction
2. When working on payroll or timesheet workflow features (e.g. payroll index, pay periods, timesheet approval), read and follow the plan at .cursor/plans/payroll_workflow_redesign_80191109.plan.md and document progress in .cursor/icr.mdx (Feature Documentation or Phase 6/7 checklist).
3. Before ending ANY response, if you've learned anything useful about project-specific architectural details that are NOT immediately obvious from reading the code, you MUST update .cursor/icr.mdx with this information
4. When updating .cursor/icr.mdx:
   - Only document reusable, cross-cutting patterns; skip single-file or one-off implementation notes that are obvious from code
   - Only add new information not already documented
   - Place information in the appropriate section, if no appropriate section exists, create one
